---
title: Chicken Sausage Skillet Orzotto All In One Pan
description: Everything is better topped with crispy, cheesy breadcrumbs. If we’re being honest, this magical mixture could be sprinkled on just about anything and we’d happily dig in, no questions asked. What makes this dish so special is that it’s already incredible on its own, so the crunchy crust is really just the cherry on top! In it, you’ll find orzo pasta, chicken sausage, and spinach, and grape tomatoes, all enrobed in a rich, lemony sauce. So, what are you waiting for?
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/one-pan-orzotto-italiano-d6e934d1.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/skillet-orzotto-italiano-5e0a4d92d56540140223ff87-df4a5729.pdf
cuisine: North America
course: main course
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 830 kcal
  fat: 32 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 90 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 49 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1640 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-sausage-skillet-orzotto-5e0a4d92d56540140223ff87
time required: 30 minutes
author: Sara Heilman
---

Heat broiler to high. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and
dry all produce. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Chop @spinach{5%oz} until you have 1
very packed cup (2 cups for 4 servings; you might not use all the spinach).
Halve @lemon{1}; cut one half into wedges. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz}.
Finely chop @parsley{1/4%oz}.

Once water is boiling, add @orzo pasta{6%oz} to #pot{}. Cook until al dente,
~{7-9%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain. Heat a large
drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a large, high-sided (preferably ovenproof)
#pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%oz} and cook,
breaking up meat into pieces, until just browned, ~{3-4%minutes}. (It'll cook
through in the next step.)

Add tomatoes and garlic to pan with sausage. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
mixture is fragrant and sausage is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in half
the @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp} (all for 4 servings); season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until tomatoes begin to break down, ~{2-3%minutes}
more. Lower heat to medium.

Stir chopped spinach, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 1/2 cup reserved pasta
cooking water (3/4 cup for 4 servings), and cooked orzo into pan. Cook, stirring,
until spinach is wilted and mixture is creamy, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> If mixture seems dry, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a
> time as necessary.

Stir in @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup} and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with
salt, pepper, and more lemon juice to taste. (TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof,
transfer mixture now to a #baking dish{}.) In a #small bowl{}, combine
@panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, a drizzle of olive oil,
salt, and pepper; sprinkle over orzotto. Broil until panko is golden brown,
~{2-3%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Divide orzotto between plates. Sprinkle with parsley. Serve with any remaining
lemon wedges on the side.